sentences.english: They prey mainly on sea lions, seals, and small toothed whales
sentences.chinese: 它们以海狮，海豹，小型齿鲸为食。

sentences.english: Smaller toothed whales are know for there feelings, or emotions for other animals.
sentences.chinese: 小齿鲸据说对别的动物有情感或情绪。

sentences.english: Later in the evolution of whale hearing, the toothed and baleen whales parted ways.
sentences.chinese: 鲸豚听觉的演化到了后期，齿鲸与须鲸就分道扬镳了。

sentences.english: We can be divided into two categories, baleen and toothed whales.
sentences.chinese: 我们可以分为两类，须鲸和齿鲸。

sentences.english: It belongs to a group of whales called toothed whales.
sentences.chinese: 它属于鲸鱼分类中一组被称之有齿鲸。

sentences.english: They are part of the family of toothed whales that also includes killer and pilot whales.
sentences.chinese: 他们的一部分，家庭齿鲸也包括杀手和试点的鲸鱼。

definition: bony fishes/Osteichthyes (taxonomic class including most fish)
cartilaginous fishes/Chondrichthyes (taxonomic class including sharks and rays)
Carnivora, order of carnivores within Mammalia
cephalopod/Cephalopoda, class of mollusks including nautilus and squid
